# 1. Purpose

This record identifies NATT-OS source code, documentation, runtime specs, audit logs, legal dossier files, and evidence artifacts for copyright and authorship tracking.

This document is not a copyright registration by itself.
It is the internal source-code record used to prepare legal filing, audit review, publication dossier, and ownership evidence.

# 2. Repository Principle

NATT-OS source assets include more than application code.

They include source code, runtime specs, .na canonical documents, .anc identity passports, .phieu runtime state, scripts, audit reports, legal dossier files, UI components, scanner rules, saved evidence artifacts, publication drafts, archived or camouflaged canonical materials.

# 3. Protected Source Groups

| Group | Examples |
|---|---|
| Core source | src/, cells, governance, engines |
| Runtime docs | docs/runtime/*.na |
| Specs | docs/specs/**/*.na, docs/specs/**/*.md |
| Legal dossier | docs/legal/*.na |
| Constitution | docs/specs/constitution/*.na |
| Memory | src/governance/memory/** |
| Dictionary | src/thienbang.si |
| Audit | audit/** |
| Evidence pages | saved HTML, saved page companion folders, screenshots, exported logs |
| Archive-like paths | archive/, docs/archive/, _deprecated/, typo-looking folders |

# 4. Archive / Evidence Rule

Archive-like paths are not trash by default.

The following must not be deleted without inventory and Gatekeeper confirmation:
- archive/
- docs/archive/
- _deprecated/
- *_files/
- saved HTML companion folders
- typo-looking folders
- duplicate-looking names
- .bak files
- files with (1), (2), or version suffixes
- old exports with unclear purpose

Rule: archive-like surface may be intentional camouflage or evidence preservation.

# 5. Git Discipline

Forbidden:
- git add .
- rm -rf archive
- rm -rf *_files
- cleanup by visual judgment
- delete orphan UI by feeling

Required:
- git add exact/path
- verify before commit
- commit only scoped files
- preserve evidence
- document removal decision

# 6. Copyright Evidence Fields

Each copyright-relevant record should preserve file path, title, creation context, author/carrier, session, commit hash, purpose, source evidence, status, public-safe boundary, internal-only boundary, and redaction requirement.

